Conclusion:</span></u></b></p>
<p class="midgray_normal" style="text-align:justify"><span lang="EN-US">Selling your 
business is one of the most important decisions you will ever make. Buyer beware 
is commonly understood, but Seller beware is equally important. There are many 
potential pitfalls for the uninformed and inexperienced seller. The 10 things 
discussed in this document are important considerations when selling Telecom 
accounts. Any transaction of this importance needs to be a win-win. Mutual 
integrity is vital. Not only must the combined expertise and experience of both 
Seller and Buyer merge into a cohesive effort, sculpting a practical plan to 
provide reasonable assurance that both parties will be satisfied, but, perhaps 
more importantly, the parties must have the competency to execute the plan with 
reasonable precision. Select a buyer with a track record of success, and a tried 
and true approach that has been proven to work in actual practice.</span></p>
